==English==

===Etymology===
From Danish ''mög-dynge'' through Middle English ''myddyng'': muck + dung.

===Noun===
'''midden'''
# A dungheap.
# A [[refuse]] heap usually near a dwelling.
# Archeological: [[prehistoric]] pile of bones and shells.

